body:
I tried creating 1000 service names in the UI to measure the impact on rendering time:

``` diff
diff --git a/zipkin-web/src/main/resources/app/js/component_ui/serviceName.js b/zipkin-web/src/main/resources/app/js/component_ui/serviceName.js
index f5b4cc6..55fb66e 100644
--- a/zipkin-web/src/main/resources/app/js/component_ui/serviceName.js
+++ b/zipkin-web/src/main/resources/app/js/component_ui/serviceName.js
@@ -23,6 +23,11 @@ define(

       this.updateServiceNameDropdown = function(ev, data) {
         $('#serviceName').empty()
+        data.serviceNames = [];
+        for (let i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {
+          data.serviceNames.push('service'+i);
+        }
+
         $.each(data.serviceNames, function(i, item) {
             $('<option>').val(item).text(item).appendTo('#serviceName');
         });
```

This basically replaces the API response with a list of service names, service0, service1, service2 ... service999.
The impact on rendering time was minimal, there was no visual cue showing that the latency was higher than when rendering 15-20 service names.

@eirslett another question, in `zipkin-web/src/main/resources/templates/v2/index.mustache` we used to have a section that was displayed on the home page (before query was executed), for example:

``` html
{{^queryResults}}
  <div class="alert alert-info" id="help-msg">
    <p>Please select the criteria for your trace lookup.</p>
  </div>
  <div id="logo"></div>
{{/queryResults}}
```

How this section never shows. Is it because the syntax `{{^queryResults}}` is no longer recognized?
